    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@NorbertUseGithub,\r\nThere is no straightforward way to pass a timeout to `ServerWriter::Write` API. \r\n\r\nHowever you could do one of the two things:\r\n- Use the Async API (i.e Use [Async Write ](https://grpc.io/grpc/cpp/classgrpc_1_1_server_async_writer.html#a467f70c7460ceb7738fb938b3bf93c85) and pass a timeout to completion queue [AsyncNext](https://grpc.io/grpc/cpp/classgrpc_1_1_completion_queue.html#a290ddf3d96e6d1d5886580e60b0602b4) . \r\n\r\n- If you want to continue to use Sync API (i.e `ServerWriter::Write`), you have perhaps have a different thread call [`ServerContext.TryCancel()`](https://grpc.io/grpc/cpp/classgrpc_1_1_server_context.html#a8569c71704f03f3b1089745228c70e3b) to cancel the RPC after some timeout.  This will cause your `SeverWriter::Write()` to return with a `false` since the call is cancelled.\r\n'\r\nHope this helps.\r\n"
  }
